  <description rain:coding="(CAP,R-D,L-P,INF),(Capacity Development,Research and Development,Lobby and Promotion,Infrastructure)" rain:description="RAIN project typology" rain:type="type" type="3">INF</description>
  <description akvo:type="6" rain:type="d_context" type="1">Recently, NEWAH has approached Water, Sanitation and Hygiene implementation utilizing a Village Development Committee (VDC) coverage approach over a longer time-frame of WASH implementation. The use of a catchment-coverage approach to WASH delivery using the principles of 3R through the RAIN Foundation aims to further NEWAHs success in WASH delivery and education by conducting a pilot application of the 3R approach in villages of Tanglichowk VDC.</description>
  <description akvo:type="8" rain:type="d_objectives" type="2">The overall objective is to increase access to water and micro irrigation system though the rain water harvesting system to the people of the Gorkha district. The specific objectives are:
1. To increased access to water 
2. To enhance capacity of the target people
3. To disseminate knowledge and skills</description>
